{"ts":"2026-04-28T12:00:00Z","agent":"ALPHA","soul_name":"GrittyGrad","issue":"trios#143","task":"ATTENTION_BACKWARD_V5","status":"REGRESS","phi_step":"EXPERIENCE","triplet":"RAIL=experience @ project=trios-trainer-igla service=v5-attn-backward sha=cd91c45 ts=2026-04-28T12:00:00Z","evidence":"v5 results WORSE than v4. seed43=2.6186(+0.43) seed44=2.6038(+0.40) seed45=2.4834(+0.29). Root cause: removed attn_down projection from gradient path. attn_down projected hidden(828)->d_model(64) and its gradient flowed correctly in v4. v5 replaced attn_down with raw embeddings fed to attention as sequence. The attention backward adds gradients for wq/wk/wv/wo (32K params) but lost the attn_down gradient path (53K params). The raw embeddings are not learnable through attention (they are shared with embed table). Hypothesis: need BOTH attn_down sequence AND attention backward. Also seq_len=8 may be too long for the current d_model=64 — attention dilutes signal across 8 positions when model only has 64 dim to represent them."}
